{"description":"Following issue will not be detected, because {{ZERO}} constraint on {{a}} is lost when evaluating conditional branch. {{NON_ZERO}} constraint on {{x}} is also lost.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n  void h() {\r\n    int x \u003d 1;\r\n    int a \u003d 0;\r\n    if (x \u003e\u003d a) {\r\n      int y \u003d 1 / a; // False negative, issue not detected\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe same problem can also lead to false positive, in case of \"suspicious call\" \r\n{code}\r\n void f() {\r\n    g(0, 1);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  private int g(int x, int y) {\r\n    if (x \u003e 0) {\r\n      return y/x;  // False positive - division by zero, when g invoked from f\r\n    } else {\r\n      return y;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n{code}\r\n","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"4.13"}